review_blob: I allowed the bottle to sit out for 10-15 min prior to opening.  It pours light copper with a thin off-white head.  Fizzes when glass is roused.  small bubbles which do not cling to the glass.Nose has an interesting contrast between hops, malt and an estery character.  Slight presence of DMS.  Flavor is bitter, woodsy, piney and spicy.  There is an underlying malt sweetness there as well.  Medium body with medium to high carbonation with a warming sensation.  this beer has a smooth balance of hops and malt but the alcohol gives it a brisk warming character.  Sticky yet dry finish.
beer_name: Nine G Infidel Imperial India Pale Ale

review_blob: Pours cloudy burnt orange with slightish white head.  Nose is very fruity and sweet-like.  Sugary.  Flavor has chewy caramel,  toffeeish character.  There is a strong citrus character like ruby-grapefruit.  Alcohol reveals itself in the finish.

Pours amber copper with smallish whitish/tan head.  Nose is Mslty with a peculiar fruityness.  Im not sure what pomegranate is like so its difficult to note these aromas as pomegranate. Flavor has a sticky sweet , caramel and malty character.  The alcohol presence is here but not overpowering.  Mild balance and medium bodymakes for more of a fallish winterlike warmer vs a summer sipping beer.  Not bad.

Pours muddy light brown with frothy tan head which disappears after about 3-4 minutes.  Very mild malty nose.  Slight caramel roasted malt.  Flavor is pungent with weak smoky character.  Not much to brag about here.
beer_name: Samuel Adams James Madison Dark Wheat Ale

review_blob: Pours yellowish gold with slight whitish head.  Nose is somewhat citrusy with underlying honey and lemony notes.  Ginger presence is mild.   Flavor has mild maltiness with faint sweetness.  Not an overpowering beer, but a nice subtle change.  Could be a nice session beer.
beer_name: Samuel Adams Traditional Ginger Honey Ale

review_blob: Pours brown with thin tan head.  Nose is malty with mild cherries and roasted, caramelly notes.  Flavor is sweet and malty, lip smacky.  Slight undertones of roasted chocolate.  Finishes with nice sticky sweetness.

Pours dirty yellow with slight whitish head.  Nose is a bit grassy and strawlike.  Slightly musty.  Thin mouthfeel, this has the makings of a "Premium" beer, with other watered down commercial examples.  Sort of boring.  Better than commercially made styles, but definitely not my fav.

Pours cloudy yellow with fluffy white head.  Nose is fruity with berry/cherry-like character, I guess a bit of currant.  Flavor has a subtle tartness with medium  body.  Almost a bit musty.  Sweet then tart, citrusy and spicy.  Finishes with a slight bitterness.

Pours burnt copper with billowing tan head. Hoppy nose noticable before bringing the glass up to note the bouquet.  Strong Cascade presence.  Malty body provides a good balance between the strong hop bitterness.  A nice drinkable beer if your prefer a hoppy beer.

PoursCopper orange with moderate off white head.  Nose has a fruity and hop-like character.  Sweet with a splash of cirtus.  Medium body with mild caramel malt flavor.  Slight bitter finish.  Not a great example of an ESB.
Pours cloudy yellow with a hint of orange.  Fluffy white head.  Nose has a blend of citrus spicyness.  Flavor has sweet fruityness with balanced spicyness.

Pours bronze orange with mild tan head.  Nose is sweet and malty but has a slight citrus character.  Flavor has mild hop bitterness to blend with caramel malty body.  This is a nice beer.  it complements itself.

Pours brown with slight bronze tint.  Slight head which disappears quickly.  Nose is sweet and malty with underlying caramel tones.  Flavor has creamy texture, not silky.  Medium body.  Sweet toasted malts with pleasant finish.
Pours yellow with fluffy white head.  Nose is straw-like and a bit grassy.  Flavor has some hint of malt sweetness, however it is overcome by a strong presence of diacetyl.  Not much going on here.

Pours muddy copper with little to no tan thin head.  Nose is sweet and biscuity.  Brown sugar and malt.  Slightly vinous which lets you sense the alcohol content.  Flavor is deep caramel and toffee.  Thick mouthfeel with a lip smacking stickiness.  Sweet finish.
beer_name: Dark Horse Scotty Karate Scotch Ale

review_blob: Pours brilliant red with pink fizzy head.  Nose has a light raspberry aroma, similat to a wine cooler.  Flavor is much of the same. Lacks true body.  There is a mild tart presence.  Alcohol is hidden well.  Nice beer to help the ladies make to transition to better quality brews.
Pours dirty brown/orange with creamy tannish head.  Nose is sweet and malty.  Flavor is pungent, tart and malty all at once.  Spicy and caramel-like. Not a bad brew to sip on.

Pours mid brown with slightish tan head.  Slightly fizzy.  Nose os mild caramel/malt with slight underlying biscuit character.  Medium to light body with flavors of mild malt and caramel/chocolate goodness.  Finishes wih slight dryness.  Fair.
Pours deep orange/brown with frothy tannish head.  Nose has biscuty, caramel malty notes.  Flavor is complex.  Malty and sweet, yet invitingly bitter at times. Nice finish.

Pours with deep yellow/orange color and moderate tannish head.  Nose has a caramel/hop character without being too overbearing.  There is a presence of a citrusy, spicy iced tea.  Flavor has stickyness but presents wih a slight lack of carbonation(despite the wax seal). Medium body.  Slight sweet finish.
Pours black and thick.  Light brown head.  Nose is sweet and chocolatey.  Oily, with lactose and burnt coffee flavor.  Syrupy.  Gets bigger as it warms.
beer_name: SKA Nefarious Ten Pin Imperial Porter

review_blob: WOW.  When I first opened the bottle, the Hop aroma erupted from the bottle before I even poured it.  Pours black with frothy light brown head.  Nose is incredibly hoppy and even a hint of citrus.   Oily with chocolate and coffee-like tones.  Well balanced.  Roasted malt character with piney/dry finish. Unique but nice beer.

Pours black with creamy thick tan head.  Nose is very roasty with hints of coffee and chocolate.  Flavor is smooth velvety bittersweet chocolate with dried fruits.  Finish is light and has slight dryness.
Pours muddy brown with moderate tan head.  Nose is sour cherries with mustyness.  Flavor is spicy with an unexplained emptiness.  Feels a bit thin.  Mild sour finish.
Pours deep brown with moderate tan head.  Nose has chololate notes.  Medium body. Mild coffee-like, malted milk and caramel.  Slight sour fininsh.
Pours light brown with smallish head.  Nose has a hint of malt with mild sweetness.  Thin body and mild caramel flavor.  Finishes without much excitement.
Pours with amber-like color with somewhat frothy tan head.  Nose has sweet malt caramel character.  Flavor is spicy yet toffee-like.  Medium body.  Clean finish.  Good session brew.
Pours very dark brown. Creamy, Guinness-like head.  Nose has chocolate and vanilla-like character.  Flavor has rich body with caramel, coffee-like and malty notes.  Bittersweet finish.  Unique brew.
Pours light orange with minimal head.  Nise is citrusy and spicy.  Medium body.  Mild malt flavor with gentle sourness in the finish.
beer_name: Two Brothers Oh Brother! Tripel Ale

review_blob: Pours dark brown, but not nearly black.  Nose has mild coffee or bittersweet character but not overpowering.  Roasted malt flavor is reminiscent ot other simple porters.  Finishes clean and perhaps a bit thin.

Pours oily black with slight tan head.  Nose is ver nice.  chocolate yet vinous in character with roasted malt sweetness.  Extremely smooth mouthfeel with velvety chocolate and licorice notes.  Alcohol blends well.  Bittersweet finish.  Great beer.
beer_name: Great Divide Yeti Imperial Stout - Oak Aged

review_blob: Pours reddish orange with off white head.  Nose has a blend of outdoors;earthy, flowerlike and mild hops.  Flavor has a mild spicy yet caramel character.  There is a noticable fruit presence which transfers to a slight sourness in the finish.  Pleasant brew.

Pours dark brown, not quite black.  Moderate tan head.  Nose presents with coffee-like chocolate notes.  Brisk.  Flavor is a smooth roasty transition to bittersweet oily chocolate and dry hop bitterness.  Well balanced brew.
beer_name: Great Divide St. Bridgets Porter (St. Brigids)

review_blob: Pours reddish brown with a creamy tan head.  Nose is nutty, malt and very light chocolate character.  Flavor is a caramel, cocoa blend with good balanced mouthfeel.  Somewhat dry in the finish.

beer_brewer_name: Portland Brewing Company (Pyramid - North American Breweries)
review_blob: Pours burnt orange with slight tannish head.  Nose is sweet and sugary with an underlyiong floral presence.  Medium balanced palate with toffee-like malt character.  Finishes with a slight bitterness.
Pours golden yellow with billowing light head.  Nose is hoppy and citrusy.  Flavor continues with cirtus character and maintains a smooth mouthfeel.  Very clean finish.
Pours reddish brown with slight tannish head.  Light nose of caramel and toasted malt.  Flavor has mild hop bitterness and medium mouthfeel.  Clean finish.

Pours dark brown with smallish tan head.  Nose is lovely roasted malt with chocolate bitterness notes.  This transfers well into the palate with coffee-like and roasted malt flavors.  Smooth mouthfeel.    Pleasant beer.

Pours hazy piss yellow with floral and high citrus nose.  Head quickly dissapates.  Flavor is overwhelmingly grapefruit.  Medium mouthfeel.  Hop bitterness makes an appearance in the finish.  Does a good job hiding the alcohol potency.

Pours orange/yellow with fluffy white head which laces nicely on the glass.  Nose is citrusy and hoppy.  Smooth mouthfeel.  Orange and citrus flavors dominate the light malta character.  Well balanced bitterness in the finish.

Pours burnt orange with nice creamy tan head.  Nose is very citrusy and light hops.  Flavor has mild hop bitterness blended with sweet piney/citrus-like notes. Moderate yet smooth mouthfeel.  Finishes with slight drying character.  Nice beer.
Pours burnt orange with little to no head.  Nose is caramel and lightly toasted malt.  Thin mouthfeel.  Flavor had mild earthy, malty nutty character.  Ho hum.

Pours copper orange with frothy tan head which disappears quickly with nice lacing on glass.  Nose is heavy hops with citrus notes.  Sweet and malty.  Flavor has sweet, fruity, biscuity character with medium body.  Finishes with slight nudge to notice the alcohol presence.
Pours dark yellow with copper tint.  Mild whitish head.  Nose is citrusy lemons and hops.  Flavor is biter, yet light caramel, biscuity notes present. Good session beer.

Pours light orange with little to no head.  
Nose is mild ginger and wheat.  Flavor is spicy and a bit citrusy.  Kind of boring.

Pours opaque with brown head with seeming red tones.  Nose is dark musty raisins, chocolate and roasted malt.  Flavor is full of dark bittersweet chocolate, cherries and molassess.  Alcohol comes and goes smoothly in the finish.
beer_name: Stoudts Fat Dog Stout (Vintages 2004 and later)

review_blob: 2002.  Pours brownish with slight mahogony tint.  Nose is very woosdy with candi sugar and maltiness.  Slightly vinous.  Full bodied, acidic with character of Flemish red/brown.  Sipping beer.

Pours black with no head.  Nose is sweet and chocolatey.  Mild alcohol presence in aroma.  Flavor is sticky,vinous and chocolate.  Improves as it lasts in the glass. Thick mouthfeel.  Bittersweet finish.  MMMM... good.

Pours dark burnt orange with literally no head.  nose is of alcohol and sweet caramel notes.  Mild oak presence.  Flavor is rich and complex.  Thick and syrupy.  Slight vanilla oakycharacter with lip smacking sweetness.  Finishes with nice alcohol burn.

Pours reddish brown with sultry tan head.  Nose is very fruity, plummy, figgy and a slight note of malt. Flavor has sweet, malty, bananna, molassess, brown sugar and mild spicyness.  Finishes a bit sticky.
